    if (_added) return;
    // CANCELLATION CHECK: if the polyline was added during a style-load
    // gap (e.g. just after a 401-triggered setStyle), `addToMap` was
    // queued on _whenStyleReady. If `clearLayer` ran between the
    // schedule and the actual fire — which is what happens when evmove5
    // re-renders routes — the layer's geoJsonIds array was reset and the
    // polyline was logically cleared. Without this guard, the queued
    // addToMap still fires later, adds source+layer to MapLibre's style,
    // and produces an ORPHAN that no future clearLayer can find (the
    // layer's tracking doesn't claim it). Symptom: "first 5 polylines
    // stay on top in true colour after route swap".
